sswort wird auf S. 356 des Buchs bzw. E-Books genannt.  aThis study investigates the function of the radio play as medium of cultural memory, based on the memories of the holocaust found in the radio plays of the GDR. In comparison to the presentation of the holocaust in other media, which has already been explored various times, here for the first time the focus is on the specific aesthetic means of the radio play and the role of radio as political instrument of power in the FRG-GDR conflict. You can now find excerpts of the radio plays analyzed in the study (previously on the CD sold with the book) under "additional material" on this webpage. The password to open the zip file can be found on p. 356 of the e-book and print edition.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aGerman dramay20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zGermany (East). 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945), in literature. 0aRadio plays, GermanxHistory and criticism. 4aGedächtnismedium. 4aHolocaust. 4aHörspiel i.d. DDR. 4aHörspiel. 4aKulturelles Gedächtnis. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aCultural Memory.  aHolocaust.  aMedium of Memory.  aRadio Play in the GDR.  aRadio Play.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2010z9783110233605oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311022589140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311022590740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110225907423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110225907/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA